column5: Hey there...been a lurker for a longtime....learning the secrets of muskie fishing lol...dont get as much time on the water as I would like to....but love the info and friendship that I have seen passed around......dont want to be that lurker anymore.  I fish at moira lake as often as I can.....looking forward to openning of season......Only question I will ask is...when does muskie season start
Welcome aboard Jason.  Being south of the border, I'm sorry that I can't answer your question.  Musky eh ?  Looking for some pics the day after.  Again - welcome to OFC !
Hey there!! Welcome to the board.  Madoc is in zone 7....so if you are fishing there, then Muskie season starts the first Saturday in June...and goes to Dec 15th.
Welcome to the Board Jason, it is a blast here    And yes there are alot of awesome people here.
Welcome Jason to the show that never ends, enjoy the ride.  Why not come to the Tyler G2G on Saturday and meet some of the group.  Great time, great food, and great prizes.  John
